        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "2193",
          "text": "I first learned about Tom Goreau’s work in 2012 when just after the UN Conference on Sustainable Development (Rio+20) Albert Bates and I attended the award ceremony of the prestigious Equator Prize Awards where Tom was one of the winners together with the team of a coral regeneration and protection project in Western Bali. It was a memorable evening with Achim Steiner and the late Rajendra Pachauri reflecting on the need for a new social contract, and Gilberto Gil rocking out on stage with Tom and the other winners.",
