        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1d56",
          "text": "Healing Marine Ecosystems",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H4"
        },
        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4ff8",
          "text": "During the last meeting in October 2019 in London, Tom and I started to explore the possibility of bringing his techniques for marine ecosystems regeneration to Mallorca and the Balearic Islands where I live. In particular, to focus on the regeneration of the seagrass meadows around the islands as an important spawning ground for marine life and one of the most significant plants for the future of marine carbon bio-sequestration.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3ace",
          "text": "Tom co-authored a book entitled ‘Innovative Methods of Marine Regeneration’ in which he draws on his life time experience in marine science and presents “new techniques for greatly increasing the recruitment, growth, survival, and resistance to stress of marine ecosystems, fisheries, and eroding shorelines, maintaining biodiversity and productivity where it would be lost.”",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 74,
              "href": "https://www.crcpress.com/Innovative-Methods-of-Marine-Ecosystem-Restoration/Goreau-Trench/p/book/9781466557734",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 33,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "124b",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*DH9dAngn_bOCTX2LLmj1gA.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "OUTSET_LEFT",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5e27",
          "text": "Over more than 30 years Tom has been a pioneer in experimenting with the use of very low (direct current) electrical stimulation applied through fine steel grids to increase the settlement rate and growth, “and reduced mortality for a wide variety of marine organisms, including corals, oysters, sponges, sea-grasses, and salt-marsh grasses.” This book documents many of the astonishing results from field experiments he as conducted around the world.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ecb0",
          "text": "Tom’s work is of huge significance as the health of the ocean is a primary determinant for planetary health and human activity has severely damaged marine ecosystems everywhere. The continued acidification of the world’s ocean and the run-away greenhouse gas release this could trigger are an existential threat to humanity and much of life on Earth. Tom’s work actively focussed on avoiding such a climate cataclysm as it offers a pathway to reversing the greenhouse gas concentrations in the atmosphere back to a safe level that would allow the warming to slow and eventually reverse as climate patterns stabilise.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "7899ec8a8698_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4f2a",
          "text": "Mallorca and the Balearics are home to many important research institutions, foundations and NGOs focussed on protecting and restoring the Balearic Seas — among them: El Centro Oceanografico de les Balears, the Mediterranean Institute for Advanced Studies, the Save the Med Foundation, the Marilles Foundation, the Mallorca Preservation Fund and the Ibiza Preservation Fund, the Palma Aquarium Foundation, and the Save Posidonia Project in Formentera.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
